1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,400
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,800
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:06,133
(Episode 31)

4
00:00:57,973 --> 00:01:01,085
Mom, you've been working nonstop all day.

5
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:06,525
Take the bedsheet and pillow cover off
and put them in the laundry room.

6
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:07,900
Put new ones on.

7
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,300
Okay.

8
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:13,235
I'll take care of my own bed,
so please get some rest.

9
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:19,433
Mom, do you want to go out
and get some fresh air with me?

10
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:20,900
Or maybe we can go watch a movie?

11
00:01:21,146 --> 00:01:23,856
Didn't you say you were on a deadline?
Go inside and write.

12
00:01:23,929 --> 00:01:26,596
I know you keep doing chores
because you're hurting inside,

13
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:28,952
but you'll really wear yourself out.

14
00:01:29,621 --> 00:01:31,000
You should really get some rest.

15
00:01:31,747 --> 00:01:34,600
I'll just finish this and then take a nap,
so don't wake me up.

16
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,967
You have to take that nap, okay?

17
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:47,900
Eun Nim, what is it?

18
00:01:48,587 --> 00:01:52,171
This is bad, Eun Ae. Mom...

19
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:53,900
What about Mom?

20
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:56,233
What?

21
00:01:58,841 --> 00:02:00,667
Okay, got it. Hang up for now.

22
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:04,536
I need to go home. I'm sorry!

23
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,195
All of a sudden?

24
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,821
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

25
00:02:14,821 --> 00:02:16,539
Dad, where are you?
I'll come down to the lobby.

26
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:17,833
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

27
00:02:40,571 --> 00:02:41,900
Manager Seo,
could you come this way for a second?

28
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,152
I'm sorry, but...

29
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:47,947
I don't really understand the sub copy.

30
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:51,488
I'm fine, so don't go out of your way.

31
00:02:51,803 --> 00:02:52,833
What? What do you mean?

32
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:56,019
You said the two of them still aren't sure
about their feelings yet.

33
00:02:56,365 --> 00:02:58,357
At least I'm sure about my own feelings,

34
00:02:58,747 --> 00:03:00,200
so I'm not going to worry
about anything else.

35
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:05,400
I'm just going to follow my heart
so I won't regret it later.

36
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:07,100
Really?

37
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:11,571
You made the right decision.
That's so like you.

38
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,000
Don't worry about anything and go.

39
00:03:27,237 --> 00:03:28,237
Okay.

40
00:03:37,435 --> 00:03:40,500
What happened? Still no word from Mom?

41
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:43,901
No. Eun Ae told me to keep an eye on Mom
before she went to work,

42
00:03:44,976 --> 00:03:46,600
but because of that stupid deadline...

43
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,557
Her phone is still turned off.

44
00:03:49,773 --> 00:03:51,331
I'm going to stop by Cho Rong's place.

45
00:03:54,448 --> 00:03:57,264
What's Eun Hyeong doing
that he's not answering his phone?

46
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:09,016
Where on earth did she go?

47
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:13,357
What? Your mom ran away from home?

48
00:04:13,597 --> 00:04:15,733
Didn't she say anything to you, Grandma?

49
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,779
I didn't see hide nor hair of her all day.

50
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,500
Do you know anywhere Mom might've gone?

51
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,299
Your mom doesn't have
any blood relatives...

52
00:04:27,299 --> 00:04:28,429
or friends.

53
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,803
All her life, she's only known home
and the real estate office.

54
00:04:30,803 --> 00:04:34,534
She's lived like a hamster on a wheel.
Where would she go?

55
00:04:34,534 --> 00:04:35,534
Still...

56
00:04:35,534 --> 00:04:37,851
Are there any places
you and Mom used to go together?

57
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,323
The market and the bathhouse
at the intersection.

58
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,100
I'll search the whole market,
so you go check the bathhouse first.

59
00:04:43,433 --> 00:04:44,433
- Okay.
- Thank you.

60
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:47,247
Please call me right away if you find her,
Grandma.

61
00:04:47,247 --> 00:04:48,247
Okay.

62
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:51,900
Where are you going, Dad?

63
00:04:51,900 --> 00:04:54,435
I thought of a few places
your mom might've gone.

64
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,900
- Let's go together on my scooter.
- Okay.

65
00:05:08,633 --> 00:05:10,800
Why is this
the only place I could come to?

66
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:12,759
Kang Yeon Ja.

67
00:05:23,005 --> 00:05:25,351
Dad, how did you know about this place?

68
00:05:25,989 --> 00:05:28,147
What kind of place is this to Mom?

69
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:31,973
It's the place
where your mom lost everything.

70
00:05:32,716 --> 00:05:33,716
What?

71
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:36,237
I want to tell you everything,

72
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,933
but if your mom can't say it herself,
I can't tell you first.

73
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,700
Anyway, if she's not here either,
where are we supposed to look for her?

74
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:47,680
Do you know where Mom's hometown is,

75
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,613
or where her parents' graves are?

76
00:05:50,181 --> 00:05:53,688
She's never gone to pay respects
or held memorial rites, but maybe...

77
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,000
This place is her hometown.

78
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:01,300
Honestly, I hope she didn't come here.

79
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,688
This won't do.
Let's report it to the police.

80
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:06,700
The police?

81
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:08,392
It hasn't been that long since she left,

82
00:06:08,392 --> 00:06:11,176
and since she's an adult, they won't file
a missing person report, but still...

83
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,296
Okay, let's go.

84
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:17,900
About Seong Jun.

85
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:21,533
He'll be joining the secretary's office
starting next week, Father.

86
00:06:22,433 --> 00:06:24,400
Really? That's good.

87
00:06:24,619 --> 00:06:28,048
Yes. That guy is diligent by default,

88
00:06:28,433 --> 00:06:31,408
and he's gone through logistics, planning,
sales, and even the production line.

89
00:06:31,408 --> 00:06:32,592
He's experienced in all kinds of areas,

90
00:06:33,204 --> 00:06:34,437
so I feel very reassured.

91
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,933
No matter how capable an employee may be,

92
00:06:38,424 --> 00:06:40,659
whether their abilities
are properly used or not...

93
00:06:41,004 --> 00:06:44,604
depends on how their superior
handles them.

94
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:46,133
Remember that.

95
00:06:47,152 --> 00:06:49,197
You can put your worries completely aside.
You know me.

96
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,581
I've spent 35 years under your wing.

97
00:06:51,581 --> 00:06:54,744
I've absorbed it all down
to my bones and muscles.

98
00:06:55,021 --> 00:06:57,216
Dinner is ready. Please come in.

99
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,333
Her timing is incredible.

100
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:01,224
Let's get up, Father.

101
00:07:01,512 --> 00:07:04,500
- Yeah, let's eat.
- Yes.

102
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:05,500
Where's Su Jeong?

103
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,200
Bonjour, madame. Bonsoir, monsieur.

104
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:10,160
Merci, merci beaucoup.

105
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,200
Merci, merci beaucoup.

106
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,600
Crystal.

107
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:20,411
Comment allez-vous?
How have you been?

108
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:23,221
Hello. Comment allez-vous?
How have you been?

109
00:07:23,677 --> 00:07:25,435
What are you doing?

110
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:27,837
Why are you interrupting me?

111
00:07:28,045 --> 00:07:29,517
Why are you suddenly studying French?

112
00:07:29,517 --> 00:07:31,109
This is all because of you.

113
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,500
You don't know?

114
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,533
I may have gotten
into the French literature department,

115
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:38,100
but I totally fell for your handsome face
and spent all my time chasing after you.

116
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:41,947
That just proves
how passionate our love was.

117
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:45,565
And besides,
I kept telling you not to skip class.

118
00:07:45,565 --> 00:07:47,528
Who was the one always ditching?

119
00:07:47,528 --> 00:07:49,600
You should've stopped me.
You should've dragged me back...

120
00:07:49,915 --> 00:07:51,720
if I were acting that immaturely.

121
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:55,100
I'm sorry I couldn't stop you back then.

122
00:07:55,533 --> 00:07:59,387
I had no idea
you still had regrets about studying.

123
00:07:59,387 --> 00:08:01,632
Regrets about studying?
I don't have any of that.

124
00:08:02,176 --> 00:08:04,700
But the other day at line dancing,

125
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:07,581
I was completely humiliated
by that real estate office lady.

126
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,100
My lousy French got exposed.

127
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,600
Lousy?

128
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:14,688
Crystal, you are going to become...

129
00:08:14,688 --> 00:08:17,176
the wife of the chairman
of the great Kangsu Group someday.

130
00:08:17,728 --> 00:08:20,800
Could you please have
a little more class in your language?

131
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,168
Starting now,
I'm going to study French seriously.

132
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:25,400
And then I'll make...

133
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,704
that woman kneel before me properly.

134
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:30,661
Fine, study.
It's not like knowledge goes to waste.

135
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:34,213
Honey, should I study abroad? In Paris.

136
00:08:35,893 --> 00:08:38,659
That sounds good. I want to go to Paris.

137
00:08:39,491 --> 00:08:41,736
Well, that's certainly a good idea,

138
00:08:42,141 --> 00:08:43,974
but Father is currently ill, you know?

139
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:47,133
Get a grip, Crystal.

140
00:08:47,133 --> 00:08:48,627
Snap out of it.

141
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:14,600
I wonder what happened. Should I call her?

142
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:18,947
You're still here?

143
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:20,600
Yes, you haven't left work yet?

144
00:09:20,896 --> 00:09:22,632
I dropped Manager Seo off
and just got back.

145
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:25,433
Finish up
and let's go grab a drink somewhere.

146
00:09:25,633 --> 00:09:26,633
There's something I want to talk about.

147
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:29,933
Let's talk after the competition is over.
I don't really have the time right now.

148
00:09:30,395 --> 00:09:32,275
Same here. I don't have the time either.

149
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:36,300
But aren't you going too far?

150
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,000
What do you mean, I'm going too far?

151
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:39,500
Do you really not know your own feelings?

152
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,144
Or are you just pretending not to know?

153
00:09:43,933 --> 00:09:47,240
Sure, whatever actions you take
are your own business,

154
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:50,776
but couldn't you
at least restrain yourself while at work?

155
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:53,000
What are you talking about right now?

156
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,600
Are you really the kind of person
who ties someone else's shoelaces?

157
00:09:56,293 --> 00:09:58,193
How do you think
the person watching that feels?

158
00:10:01,133 --> 00:10:04,555
I'm asking you,
please stop making Seung Ri suffer.

159
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:07,300
I'm leaving.

160
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:17,803
You couldn't find her either?

161
00:10:18,233 --> 00:10:21,033
No. We went everywhere she might've gone,
but she wasn't there.

162
00:10:21,033 --> 00:10:23,832
My goodness, Cho Rong and I...

163
00:10:23,832 --> 00:10:28,200
searched the whole market
and bathhouse high and low,

164
00:10:28,648 --> 00:10:31,363
but no one saw Yeon Ja today.

165
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:35,413
Grandma, what should we do?
A group reservation just came in.

166
00:10:35,413 --> 00:10:37,600
A group? Just turn them away.

167
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,000
No, ma'am.
Please go take care of your work.

168
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,656
We'll keep looking for her.

169
00:10:42,288 --> 00:10:44,091
Is now really the time
to worry about business?

170
00:10:44,091 --> 00:10:47,344
Grandma, please go on ahead.
We'll find Mom.

171
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:51,333
Don't worry too much.
She will come back safely.

172
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:53,072
Okay. Hurry and get back to work.

173
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,136
Thank you, Grandma.

174
00:10:55,136 --> 00:10:58,056
Why are you thanking me?

175
00:10:58,056 --> 00:10:59,168
Are we strangers?

176
00:10:59,656 --> 00:11:00,656
Let's go.

177
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:05,027
- Hello.
- My goodness. Hi.

178
00:11:06,584 --> 00:11:08,027
What happened? Still no news about Mom?

179
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:09,937
How can you only be showing up now?

180
00:11:10,128 --> 00:11:12,200
Sorry, I was teaching
and couldn't check my phone.

181
00:11:12,300 --> 00:11:13,832
Teaching? What do you mean?

182
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:16,744
Well, I teach kids at a cram school.

183
00:11:17,112 --> 00:11:18,000
I'll explain later.

184
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:21,500
Dad, how about we file
a missing person report with the police?

185
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,413
I already went to the police station
with Eun Ae,

186
00:11:23,413 --> 00:11:26,043
but since she's an adult
and there are no signs of foul play yet,

187
00:11:26,533 --> 00:11:28,187
they said they wouldn't accept
a missing person report.

188
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:30,400
So we just left
her personal information there for now.

189
00:11:30,608 --> 00:11:34,133
There's no way she's thinking
of doing anything bad, right?

190
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,840
Cho Eun Nim,
how could you say something so awful?

191
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,064
Your mom would never do
something extreme...

192
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:39,960
while worrying about us.

193
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,840
So none of you should be having
such horrible thoughts.

194
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,600
None of you have eaten, right?
I'll get the food ready.

195
00:11:47,072 --> 00:11:49,805
Eun Ae,
we can't eat in a situation like this.

196
00:11:50,139 --> 00:11:51,700
Mom woke up at dawn...

197
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:54,136
to make soup and side dishes
so we wouldn't go hungry.

198
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:57,725
If we understand even a little
of how Mom feels, we should eat first.

199
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,100
Yeah, let's do that, okay?

200
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,033
("Wild Rose")

201
00:12:24,984 --> 00:12:30,304
<i>On the way to Mom's work</i>

202
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:34,400
<i>White wild rose</i>

203
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:40,037
<i>Wild rose</i>

204
00:12:46,027 --> 00:12:47,427
<i>Good</i>

205
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,500
Are you okay?

206
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:20,233
Thank you.

207
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:25,400
I forgot to return this to her.

208
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,700
Is her husband doing all right?

209
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,035
Don't cry, Mom.

210
00:14:10,003 --> 00:14:12,300
I can wait.

211
00:14:13,376 --> 00:14:15,100
I'll eat well,

212
00:14:15,856 --> 00:14:18,939
sleep well, and never cry.

213
00:14:19,899 --> 00:14:23,033
If I can't sleep,
I can just sing "Wild Rose."

214
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:27,900
All right.

215
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,700
Good girl, my Yeon Sun.

216
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,900
Don't go anywhere, and wait here.

217
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,500
Mom will come back for you soon.

218
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:43,900
- Please come out quickly.
- Yes.

219
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,300
Yeong Hwa, let's go.

220
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:53,600
You have to wait here.

221
00:14:55,933 --> 00:14:57,400
Please hurry out.

222
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,400
Yes, we're coming.

223
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:20,100
<i>On the way to Mom's work</i>

224
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:23,300
<i>White wild rose</i>

225
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:29,700
<i>The white petals of the wild rose</i>

226
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:34,533
<i>Taste good too</i>

227
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:38,133
Why aren't you coming, Mom?

228
00:15:39,533 --> 00:15:43,229
Ten nights, twenty nights,
thirty nights have all passed.

229
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,833
Come quickly, Mom.

230
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:49,900
(Samdae Diner)

231
00:15:53,433 --> 00:15:54,433
Follow me.

232
00:15:54,637 --> 00:15:56,096
Where are we going?

233
00:15:56,096 --> 00:15:57,133
Stop talking, and follow me.

234
00:15:57,133 --> 00:16:01,400
No. My mom said she'd come back for me.

235
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:04,208
She told me I had to wait here.

236
00:16:04,208 --> 00:16:05,900
She won't come back for you.

237
00:16:06,181 --> 00:16:08,237
That woman abandoned her own daughter
to change her fate.

238
00:16:08,517 --> 00:16:09,805
- Come on already.
- No.

239
00:16:09,805 --> 00:16:13,307
My mom didn't abandon me.
She didn't abandon me!

240
00:16:13,307 --> 00:16:15,000
Seriously, hurry and follow me!

241
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:18,800
No, my mom said she'd come back for me.

242
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:20,733
- Follow me.
- Mom!

243
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:23,165
Mom!

244
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,700
Like an idiot.

245
00:16:31,232 --> 00:16:32,799
Why did I bring this with me?

246
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,833
Where are you, Yeon Sun?

247
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,633
You're alive, right?

248
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,800
Grandma.

249
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,773
You're home late.

250
00:17:21,033 --> 00:17:22,533
What's the matter?

251
00:17:24,133 --> 00:17:25,133
It's just...

252
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,600
There's someone I've missed
for a very long time,

253
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,600
and today especially,
I keep thinking about them.

254
00:17:32,746 --> 00:17:34,067
Someone you miss?

255
00:17:34,461 --> 00:17:38,235
Silly me, talking about this to someone
who just came home exhausted from work.

256
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,992
What should I get you?

257
00:17:39,992 --> 00:17:42,700
No, Grandma. I was heading upstairs,

258
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:44,600
but I saw the kitchen light on,
so I came to check.

259
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,033
Is there anything I can help you with?

260
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:50,739
No, don't worry, and go upstairs to rest.

261
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,400
I'm going to bed now.

262
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,179
Okay. Good night, Grandma.

263
00:18:05,133 --> 00:18:07,700
I was worried this morning
when she kept making...

264
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:08,971
so many side dishes,

265
00:18:10,932 --> 00:18:14,632
but I never imagined
she was preparing to leave home.

266
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,400
The braised beef I like,

267
00:18:19,059 --> 00:18:20,592
the grilled pollack Dad likes.

268
00:18:21,373 --> 00:18:23,033
They're all dishes we like.

269
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:27,933
But I don't really know what Mom liked.

270
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:32,300
Dad and all of us betrayed Mom,

271
00:18:33,533 --> 00:18:35,500
but even until the end,
she only thought about us.

272
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,433
I really can't eat this.

273
00:18:40,733 --> 00:18:43,533
Don't be like that.
Think of all the care Mom put into this...

274
00:18:43,745 --> 00:18:44,745
and eat up.

275
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:48,300
We need to eat, cheer up, and find Mom.

276
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,600
You really did that, sweetie?

277
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:06,700
- Yeah, Mom.
- My daughter is so adorable.

278
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,300
I wonder if they've eaten yet.

279
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,833
Why are there so many calls?

280
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:40,400
(Eldest Daughter, Husband,
Eldest Daughter, Younger Daughter)

281
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:50,083
- Hello?
- Is this Ms. Kang Yeon Ja?

282
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,019
This is the Onhwa Police Station.

283
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:54,400
What? The police station?

284
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,100
Are you all right?

285
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:58,400
Your family said they were going
to file a missing person report.

286
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,403
A missing person report? What nonsense.

287
00:20:03,745 --> 00:20:05,165
It's not like that.

288
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:08,360
I just came out for some fresh air
for a bit.

289
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:11,296
Then please call your family.

290
00:20:11,653 --> 00:20:13,953
It's chaos for them right now.
Please call them.

291
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:16,069
Okay, understood.

292
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:22,133
(Eldest Daughter)

293
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,949
- What is it?
- Mom!

294
00:20:28,033 --> 00:20:30,587
Where are you, Mom?
Where are you right now?

295
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,833
- At a hotel.
- A hotel?

296
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,829
What hotel? Which hotel are you at?

297
00:20:36,154 --> 00:20:37,521
Eun Ae, let me talk to her.

298
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:42,029
Mom, tell me where you are.
I'll come there right now.

299
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:43,500
Let's meet and talk.

300
00:20:44,027 --> 00:20:45,360
Why would you come here?

301
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:49,541
I've never traveled alone even once
in my life.

302
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:53,800
Don't ruin my very first solo trip.

303
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:58,027
If you were going on a trip,
you should've at least left a note.

304
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,285
Why has your phone been off
this whole time?

305
00:21:00,707 --> 00:21:02,307
I didn't realize the battery had died.

306
00:21:02,424 --> 00:21:03,424
Really, Mom?

307
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:06,000
Nothing's really going on, right?

308
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:10,341
Yeah. I'll clear my head for a few days
and then come back,

309
00:21:10,591 --> 00:21:11,891
so stop calling so much.

310
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,033
Okay, Mom.

311
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:17,600
But regardless of who you call,
you have to contact us...

312
00:21:17,827 --> 00:21:19,227
at least once a day, okay?

313
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,941
Okay. Once a day,

314
00:21:22,651 --> 00:21:25,941
I'll report whether I'm dead or alive,
happy?

315
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:27,400
Let me talk to her.

316
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:30,100
It's me, honey.

317
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:37,437
Honey.

318
00:21:37,437 --> 00:21:38,547
Yeon Ja.

319
00:21:39,133 --> 00:21:40,933
Why? Did Mom hang up?

320
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:46,833
It seems
she still doesn't want to talk to me.

321
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:48,939
Eun Ae, why didn't you let me talk to her?

322
00:21:49,133 --> 00:21:50,800
There's something
I really need to say to Mom.

323
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:54,800
She said she'd contact us once every day,

324
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:58,333
so next time we talk to her,
I'll definitely find out where she is.

325
00:21:58,333 --> 00:21:59,600
Please don't worry too much.

326
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,264
Yeah, just hearing her voice
makes me feel relieved.

327
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:05,856
Eun Hyeong, you should go home now.

328
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,400
You have work again tomorrow, so go rest.

329
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:09,900
Okay, I will.

330
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:13,147
Right, take some side dishes with you.

331
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:16,533
Mom even labeled some containers for you.

332
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:34,240
Mom, you have to come back home...

333
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:38,133
smiling brightly like this again, okay?

334
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:43,900
He scared me. Seriously.

335
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:48,600
Bravo.

336
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:56,264
If he finds out I have this picture,
he'll be furious.

337
00:22:58,533 --> 00:22:59,833
(Team Manager Ko Gyeol)

338
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:00,900
What?

339
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:04,333
Yes, Team Manager.

340
00:23:05,433 --> 00:23:06,651
Sorry for calling so late.

341
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:09,900
What's going on exactly? Can I know too?

342
00:23:11,168 --> 00:23:14,200
Actually, my mom ran away from home.

343
00:23:14,629 --> 00:23:16,662
What? Ran away?

344
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:20,500
Our whole family took turns
making things hard for her.

345
00:23:21,635 --> 00:23:25,400
But we got word
that she's safe and doing well.

346
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:27,800
That's really a relief.

347
00:23:29,233 --> 00:23:31,200
Are you done preparing
for the presentation?

348
00:23:31,533 --> 00:23:33,600
Of course.
Did you think I couldn't prepare for it...

349
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,232
just because you weren't there?

350
00:23:35,833 --> 00:23:37,288
No, that's not what I meant.

351
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:40,600
I'm sorry. We're nearing the competition,

352
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,579
but I've only caused concern
because of my personal problems.

353
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:47,640
If you're really that sorry,
shall we do a rehearsal right now?

354
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:51,200
What? Are you telling me
to come to the office right now?

355
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:54,915
No, let's do a video call.

356
00:23:55,733 --> 00:23:57,100
A video call?

357
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,900
Why? Is there a problem?

358
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:02,100
No. As a team member,
it's obviously something I should do...

359
00:24:03,033 --> 00:24:05,000
Let's start in ten minutes.

360
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,400
Ten minutes. Okay.

361
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:17,500
Let's begin.

362
00:24:19,033 --> 00:24:21,664
I'm Ko Gyeol, Team Two Manager
of the Kangsu Retirement Community.

363
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,400
I stand here as a team manager,

364
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:26,019
but at the same time, as an architect...

365
00:24:26,019 --> 00:24:29,400
Wait. We said you'd make eye contact
with the judges...

366
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,600
and speak
as if you're having a conversation.

367
00:24:31,300 --> 00:24:33,133
Think of me as one of the judges,

368
00:24:33,133 --> 00:24:35,033
make eye contact with me, and try again.

369
00:24:35,033 --> 00:24:38,100
What? Make eye contact?

370
00:24:41,900 --> 00:24:46,000
Architecture is about creating spaces,
but ultimately the people...

371
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:50,221
Team Manager, you're suddenly
talking fast and stumbling.

372
00:24:50,433 --> 00:24:51,433
Again.

373
00:24:53,394 --> 00:24:54,561
Yes, again.

374
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,900
Good. Again.

375
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:02,773
Architecture is a process, not a result,
and within it, repeated...

376
00:25:07,149 --> 00:25:10,485
Intern Cho Eun Ae,
are you getting sleepy right now?

377
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:12,869
Your team manager is practicing
until his voice is hoarse.

378
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:16,077
I'm sorry. Please continue.

379
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:22,833
Let's take a five-minute break.

380
00:25:36,115 --> 00:25:37,701
Did you sleep well?

381
00:25:38,769 --> 00:25:40,769
Did you just wake up,
or are you about to go to bed now?

382
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:44,000
I haven't slept yet,
and I'm trying not to sleep.

383
00:25:44,821 --> 00:25:46,588
- What?
- Dad told me,

384
00:25:46,733 --> 00:25:48,200
to give it everything I've got.

385
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:50,163
So I haven't slept a wink,

386
00:25:50,163 --> 00:25:53,100
and I'm doing my absolute best
with all my strength.

387
00:25:53,745 --> 00:25:56,045
Even if you're doing your best,
do it smartly.

388
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:58,300
Things don't work
just because you use brute force.

389
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,853
Brute force?

390
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:02,670
Did you just call me stupid?

391
00:26:03,335 --> 00:26:04,355
Here we go again!

392
00:26:04,933 --> 00:26:06,900
How old are you two?
Every time you see each other...

393
00:26:08,633 --> 00:26:09,733
But where's Dad?

394
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:11,833
He left early this morning
to go to the Chairman's house.

395
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,100
What's the title of that novel again?

396
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:17,800
Why? Do you want to read it too?

397
00:26:18,033 --> 00:26:21,309
I just want to see
what kind of work it is...

398
00:26:21,309 --> 00:26:22,975
that has you this obsessed. Why?

399
00:26:22,975 --> 00:26:25,775
"The ER Witch."
The title is "The ER Witch."

400
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:29,179
After you read it, please like,
subscribe, turn on notifications,

401
00:26:29,959 --> 00:26:31,259
give feedback after finishing it,

402
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:33,603
and add it to your favorites list too,
okay?

403
00:26:36,133 --> 00:26:37,200
Why is there so much to do?

404
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,379
If you're going to be like this,

405
00:26:46,379 --> 00:26:47,875
why don't you just move back in altogether
and stay in the annex?

406
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:53,033
Go on in. The chairman is waiting.

407
00:26:53,033 --> 00:26:54,033
Yes, ma'am.

408
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:57,900
You should have breakfast. Come quickly.

409
00:26:57,900 --> 00:26:58,900
Yes, Mother.

410
00:27:02,033 --> 00:27:04,633
Did Mr. Seo find some kind of clue?

411
00:27:05,532 --> 00:27:06,532
A clue?

412
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:10,059
You've seen it too. He's been coming
and going before breakfast every day.

413
00:27:13,733 --> 00:27:14,733
This photo...

414
00:27:15,347 --> 00:27:18,100
It's an estimated face...

415
00:27:18,476 --> 00:27:20,976
based on the photo inside the necklace
and the current photo of Madam.

416
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:03,300
(Our Happy Days)

417
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:05,600
So meticulous as always.

418
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:07,643
Where do people usually hide keys?

419
00:28:07,643 --> 00:28:09,200
- What are you doing?
- You startled me.

420
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,933
- Mom!
- Hey!

421
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:14,960
You know the opposing team's strategy
is top secret, right?

422
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,479
Ko Gyeol, take it easy already.

423
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:19,733
Looks like spring is finally coming
for our Cho Eun Ae.

424
00:28:19,733 --> 00:28:22,000
Did he suggest the rehearsal on purpose
so I could get some sleep?

425
00:28:22,672 --> 00:28:24,200
What am I even thinking right now...

426
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:26,100
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
